- 'Rotate' commands are a type of command in the system that instructs robots to perform rotation actions;
- The date range for the query is October 2023, which includes all days from October 1 to October 31;
- The query filters out commands that were not executed by a robot, ensuring only robot-executed commands are considered;
- The condition `COUNT(p.metric_id) > 10` ensures that only command types with more than 10 performance metric entries are included in the final results.

- 'specific type' refers to `command_type` = 1;
- 'high speed' refers to `speed` > 100;
- 'high torque' refers to `torque_limit` > 20;
- 'more than a certain number of executions' refers to `total_execution_count` > 5.
